The paper deals with the dynamic allocation of spectrum in the 3.5 GHz band, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses interference and coexistence issues, which are relevant to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving optimization problems, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
